description:
&lt;p&gt;This is a rare and exciting opportunity to lead a successful, well-established, enthusiastic and experienced mental health research team in Leeds and York. Alongside the three Clinical Leads for R&amp;D, you will continue to expand research capacity and expertise across the Trust. You will work with our mental health, dementia and learning disability service users and carers and with a wide range of collaborators ie academic, commercial, other NHS trusts, education, local authorities and third sector.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;be an innovative leader with ideas of how to work well with clinicians, academics and other staff to develop research questions that improve people’s health&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;manage the departmental budget including grant income (£7m), Clinical Research Network and commercial income, making best use of this to deliver our strategic plans and&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;support and increase the opportunities for staff from all professions along the clinical academic career pathways.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a Masters or PhD, experience of managing a team in a complex organisation, adapting to change, inspiring staff and making a positive impact on people’s health through research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**Please note any correspondence following application will be sent via trac.jobs &amp; the Trust&#39;s Resourcing Team**&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMax Henderson 07980 957759 / Alison Thompson 07980 958811&lt;/p&gt;
